      <bioghist id="aspace_418c594cf92fba574e70eb1dff21ea8a">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Fitz-Greene Halleck (1790-1867), poet.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a122bb9d53b8886472f55c6fd977af28">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Collection consists of letters from Halleck, autograph manuscripts of several poems, and a day book. Correspondence, all autograph letters, signed, includes letters to John Bell Bouton and Frederic S. Cozzens. The "Day Book N. 10, R. Elliot" of Guilford, Connecticut, in the hand of Halleck, documents accounts for the period from June 1809 to May 1810.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_fac579546733c0f05bc3046da82d9eb0">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Acquired from various sources.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <processinfo id="aspace_fc15422573f2c498eb90d2ca510d8ceb">
